I"ß<h2 id="how-to-verify-signatures-for-downloadable-artifacts">How to verify signatures for downloadable artifacts</h2>

<p>Download our PGP key using the link below and import it.</p>

<p>If youâ€™re using gpg, you just need to run:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gpg --import /path/to/key
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>You can then verify the signature by downloading it into the same directory where you downloaded the tarball, and running:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gpg --verify /path/to/signature /path/to/tarball
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>It should show a good signature signed by opensearch@amazon.com.</p>

